However, it is important to note that, in cases of domestic abuse, it is not more important to maintain one’s relationship, because often these abusive relationships can lead to destruction of one’s mental and physical self.

We are challenged with a mental health crisis due to COVID-19 and I believe the pandemic has played a part in colourful marriages breaking down. I do not believe women are breaking down marriages as a means of escape, or as a part of some feminist movement that contends women are rejecting marriage in favour of the freedom of single life. You only have to sit on social media for an hour and you will recognise the widespread domestic abuse. There are some women who are willing to live with the abuse, but many women are unhappy, frustrated, depressed, retiring to the bedroom or swimming pool, or giving birth so they can make plans to leave.

You cannot negate a woman’s experience

How many cases have been registered with TTTFDS? How women are being highlighted and affirmed on social media? How many cases have been reported to the police? How many divorced/divorcing/unmarried women approached the TTTFDS for support?

Why is there such a rush to define what is a bad marriage or divorce, as opposed to providing support to get away safely and sustain relationships?
